 10  # Bilinear form
 11  
 12  This file defines a bilinear form over a module. Basic ideas
 13  such as orthogonality are also introduced, as well as reflexivive,
 14  symmetric and alternating bilinear forms.
 15  
 16  A bilinear form on an R-module V, is a function from V x V to R,
 17  that is linear in both arguments
 18  
 19  ## Notations
 20  
 21  Given any term B of type bilin_form, due to a coercion, can use
 22  the notation B x y to refer to the function field, ie. B x y = B.bilin x y.
 23  
 24  ## References
 25  
 26  * <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilinear_form>
 27
